plt.show()

Part III:¶

Model prediction :: Classification: Profit or Loss¶

In [220]:
def model_confussion_matrix_score():
    from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix
    cm=confusion_matrix(test_y,voting_clf.predict(test_x))
    plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
    sns.heatmap(cm,annot=True,fmt='.5g',linewidths=.5,square=True,cmap='Blues_r')
    plt.xlabel("Actual label")
    plt.ylabel("Predict Label")
    print(f'*********************************************************')
    print(f'Model score:{voting_clf.score(test_x,test_y)}')
    print(f'*********************************************************')
    print(classification_report(test_y,voting_clf.predict(test_x)))
    print(f'*********************************************************')
